IndividualPolicy_Name: Total or partial exemption from Impuesto a los Combustibles Liquidos y Gaseosos (ICLG) or hydrocarbon tax
Description: Biodiesel
Short_Description: Biodiesel
Notes: Minimum tax rate of Diesel-oil ARS/l 0,15
Measure_Description: Biodiesel in the domestic market is exempt from the taxes on petroleum fuels: (i) the 20% Impuesto a los Combustibles Liquidos y Gaseosos (ICLG), or hydrocarbon tax; (ii) the 20% tasa de gasoil (diesel tax).

Short_Description: Biodiesel
Notes: The Cleaner Fuels Grant Scheme will be reduced to zero from 1 July 2015 and from 1 July 2016 the excise rate for biodiesel will be increased for five years. It is assumed that the rate of increase in the excise rate for biodiesel is equal to the one of et

Description: Biodiesel
Short_Description: Biodiesel
Notes: A carbon tax is levied on the carbon content of fuels. Emissions from the combustion of biofuels are excluded. The carbon price is fixed at $23 tonne in 201213, $24.15 in 201314 and $25.40 in 201415. From 201516 the price will be set by the market.; D
Measure_Description: Biofuel is regarded as 'zero rated' for carbon emissions. The carbon charge is given by multiplying the carbon price (AUD/CO2 tonne) and the carbon emissions rate by fuel type (0.0027 carbon dioxide-equivalent emissions rate per litre/kilogram of diesel).
Title_Of_Notice: 2011 Clean Energy Act, Act No. 131 of 2011 as amended, taking into account amendments up to Statute Law Revision Act 2013

Notes: The Ethanol Production Grants (EPG) will cease from 1 July 2015 and excise taxes will be progressively applied to ethanol
Measure_Description: Ethanol Production Grants Programme to be ceased on 30 June 2015; fuel excise on domestically produced ethanol to be reduced to zero from 1 July 2015 then increased by 2.5 cents per litre per year for five years from 1 July 2016 till it reaches 12.5 cents

Description: Ethanol
Short_Description: Ethanol
Notes: A carbon tax is levied on the carbon content of fuels. Emissions from the combustion of biofuels are excluded. The carbon price is fixed at $23 tonne in 201213, $24.15 in 201314 and $25.40 in 201415. From 201516 the price will be set by the market.; D
Measure_Description: Biofuel is regarded as 'zero rated' for carbon emissions. The carbon charge is given by multiplying the carbon price (AUD/CO2 tonne) and the carbon emissions rate by fuel type (0.0024 carbon dioxide-equivalent emissions rate per litre/kilogram of petrol).
Title_Of_Notice: 2011 Clean Energy Act, Act No. 131 of 2011 as amended, taking into account amendments up to Statute Law Revision Act 2013

Description: Ethanol
Short_Description: Ethanol
Notes: The carbon tax mechanism existing under the Clean Energy Act 2011 has been repealed as from 1 July 2014. Liable entities must still meet their carbon price obligations for the 2013-2014 financial year. Date of registration is used for date of publication.
Title_Of_Notice: Clean Energy Legislation (Carbon Tax Repeal) Act 2014 - n. 83, 2014
Legal_Basis_Name: Clean Energy Legislation (Carbon Tax Repeal) Act 2014

Measure_Description: Maximum reference price (Preços Máximos de Referência-PMR). Biofuel purchases occurr though a public auction system (7/11/2005). The federal government sets the maximum sales price at each auction and the final price must be lower than that price.

Short_Description: Ethanol
Notes: Changes in mandatory blending requirements occur on a monthly basis, not yearly. For that reason, it was calculated the average of these monthly blends in order to obtain the respective annual blend; % of ethanol that must be blended into gasoline.

Legal_Basis_Name: Several Decrees and Resolutions of Ministry of Agriculture, Livestock and Food Supply (MAPA)

IndividualPolicy_Name: Total or partial exemption from ICMS (consumption state tax for circulation of goods and services)
Description: Ethanol
Short_Description: Ethanol
Notes: At the state level, there are different tax regimes for the ICMS (consumption state tax for circulation of goods and services). ICMS charged on ethanol varies from 12% to 27%, with most states charging 25%. ICMS for gasoline varies from 25% to 31%.
Measure_Description: ICMS (consumption state tax for circulation of goods and services)
Benchmark_Tax: ICMS (consumption state tax for circulation of goods and services)

Condition: Imports of biodiesel originating in Argentina
Description: Biodiesel and mixtures thereof, not containing or containing less than 70 % by weight of petroleum oils or oils obtained from bituminous minerals - Other -- Blends containing by weight more than 20 % of fatty-acid mono-alkyl esters or of a mixture of fatt
Short_Description: (-) Blends containing by weight more than 20% of fatty-acid mono-alkyl esters or of a mixture of fatty-acid mono-alkyl esters and paraffinic gasoil obtained from synthesis and/or hydro-treatment, of non-fossil origin. From Canada
Notes: Measures in force (Provisional.). Investigation ongoing.  The measure applies to 3824909701, 3824909703, 3824909704, 3826001000, 3826009011, 3826009019, 3826009030.
Measure_Description: The product allegedly being dumped is from Argentina. The allegation is based on a comparison of the domestic price with the export price. The countries have a system of differentiated export taxes, that seems to distort dom. prices of key raw materials.

Measure_Description: The allegation of dumping is based on a comparison of the domestic price with the export price of the product when sold for export to the Union. Domestic prices of the key raw material appear to be distorted due to a system of differentiated export taxes.
